  "eprint": {
    "title": "Cryptanalysis of an Anonymous Authentication and Key Agreement Protocol for Secure Wireless Body Area Network",
    "authors": [
      {
        "name": "Mohammad Amin Rakeei",
        "email": "rakeei@mail",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Farokhlagha Moazami",
        "email": "",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "Recently, Kumar and Chand proposed an\nanonymous authentication protocol for wireless body area\nnetwork. They claimed that their scheme meets major security\nrequirements and is able to resist known attacks. However, in this\npaper we demonstrate that their scheme is prone to traceability\nattack. Followed by this attack, an attacker can launch a man-in-the-middle attack and share a session key with the victim node,\nand hence the scheme does not achieve secure authentication. Also,\nwe show that this protocol does not provide perfect forward\nsecrecy which considered as a key security property in the design\nof any secure key agreement protocol.",
    "keywords": [
      "Wireless body area network (WBAN)",
      "perfect forward secrecy",
      "traceability",
      "man-in-the-middle (MITM)",
      "authentication"
    ],
    "category": "Cryptographic protocols",
    "publication_info": "Preprint. MINOR revision.",
